  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the process to get a job at Wipro?",
  "response": "Getting a job at Wipro, a global information technology, consulting, and business process services company, typically involves several steps. Here's a general outline of the process:\n\n1. **Research and Preparation**:\n   - Understand Wipro's business model, values, and the services they offer.\n   - Familiarize yourself with the job roles available and the skills required for those positions.\n   - Prepare your resume and tailor it to highlight relevant skills and experiences.\n\n2. **Job Search**:\n   - Visit the Wipro careers website or job portals like LinkedIn, Indeed, or Naukri to find open positions.\n   - Look for openings that match your qualifications and interests.\n\n3. **Application**:\n   - Submit your application through the Wipro careers portal or the specific job listing.\n   - Ensure all required documents, such as your resume and cover letter, are included.\n\n4. **Initial Screening**:\n   - After your application is submitted, the recruitment team will review it. If your profile matches the job requirements, you may be contacted for an initial screening.\n\n5. **Aptitude and Technical Tests**:\n   - Many candidates are required to take an online assessment or aptitude test that evaluates quantitative, verbal, and logical reasoning skills.\n   - Depending on the role, you may also have to complete a technical test relevant to your field.\n\n6. **Technical Interview**:\n   - If you pass the initial tests, you will likely be invited for a technical interview. This may involve problem-solving questions, coding challenges (for IT roles), and technical discussions related to your field of expertise.\n\n7. **HR Interview**:\n   - Successful candidates from the technical round are usually called for an HR interview. This interview assesses your fit within the company culture, your career goals, and your understanding of the role.\n\n8. **Offer Letter**:\n   - If you perform well in both interviews, you may receive a job offer. The HR team will communicate the details of the offer, including salary, benefits, and other terms.\n\n9. **Onboarding**:\n   - After accepting the offer, you will go through the onboarding process, which includes completing necessary paperwork, training, and orientation.\n\n### Tips for Success:\n- **Networking**: Connect with current or former Wipro employees to gain insights and possibly referrals.\n- **Preparation**: Practice common interview questions and technical problems related to the job you\u2019re applying for.\n- **Stay Updated**: Keep up with the latest industry trends, especially in technology and consulting, as this knowledge can be beneficial during interviews.\n\nBy following these steps and preparing adequately, you can improve your chances of securing a job at Wipro.",
